#### Before Everything
The solution is I learned from **labuladong.** 
https://labuladong.gitee.io/algo/2/18/27/
#### Idea
For solving the problem, with the view of <u>the current root</u>, we need to know following things:
+  `sum` of left subtree and right subtree
+  `min` of right subtree
+  `max` of left subtree
+  `isBST` of leftSubtree

Because only following conditions, can we update the global variable`maxSum` which stores the possible answer:
+ left subtree is BST, right subtree is BST
+ current tree is BST

So we use an array to store the result of each tree
```java
// int[] res = new int[]{sum, min, max, isBST}
int[] res = new int[4]; 
```
Convert two conditions into mathematical expression:
```java
// left subtree is BST, right subtree is BST
left[3] == 1 && right[3] == 1;
// current tree is BST
// i.e., the value of root should less than min of right subtree and greater than max of left subtree
root.val > left[2] && root.val < right[1];
```
When  the conditions are satisfied, we can update the global variable `maxSum`
```java
 this.maxSum = Math.max(curr[0], this.maxSum);
```
#### Code
```

/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    int maxSum = 0;
    public int maxSumBST(TreeNode root) {
        traverse(root);
        return this.maxSum;
    }

    // int[] sum = {sum, min, max, isBST}
    private int[] traverse(TreeNode root){
        // base case
        if(root == null){
            return new int[]{0, Integer.MAX_VALUE, Integer.MIN_VALUE, 1};
        }
        // left
        int[] left = traverse(root.left);
        // right
        int[] right = traverse(root.right);
        // root
        // check left and right is BST or not, if so, check if root and min and max okay, then update sum
        int[] curr = new int[4];
        if(left[3] == 1 && right[3] == 1 && root.val > left[2] && root.val < right[1]){
            curr[3] = 1;
            curr[0] = left[0] + right[0] + root.val;
            curr[1] = Math.min(root.val, left[1]);
            curr[2] = Math.max(root.val, right[2]);
            this.maxSum = Math.max(curr[0], this.maxSum);
        }else{
            curr[3] = 0;
        }
        return curr;

    }
}
```

