solutions.content:
I use post-order traverse. For each node return an array of 3 elements.
- 1st element: minimum value in the tree
- 2nd element: maximum value in the tree
- 3rd element: sum of all elements in the tree

Special case:
- leaf node: return {null, null, 0}
- node that is not a binary search tree: return null


```
class Solution {
    private int res = 0;

    public int maxSumBST(TreeNode root) {
        postorder(root);
        return res;
    }

    private Integer[] postorder(TreeNode root) {
        if (root == null) return new Integer[]{null, null, 0}; // min, max, sum

        Integer[] left = postorder(root.left);
        Integer[] right = postorder(root.right);

        boolean isLeftBST = left != null && (left[1] == null || (left[1] != null && root.val > left[1]));
        boolean isRightBST = right != null && (right[0] == null || (right[0] != null && root.val < right[0]));

        if (!isLeftBST || !isRightBST) return null; // not BST

        int sum = root.val + left[2] + right[2];
        res = Math.max(res, sum);

        int min = left[0] == null ? root.val : Math.min(root.val, left[0]);
        int max = right[1] == null ? root.val : Math.max(root.val, right[1]);

        return new Integer[]{min, max, sum};
    }
}
```

