solutions.content:
Given an integer `n`, return a string of length `n` so that each character in the string occurs odd number of times.

# Explanation

Just consider two cases: `n % 2 = 0` and `n % 2 = 1`.

If `n % 2 = 0`, return 1 "a" and `n-1` "b"s.

If `n % 2 = 1`, return `n` "a"s.

# C++ Solution

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    string generateTheString(int n) {
        string ans;
        if (n % 2 == 1) {
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
                ans += "a";
        }
        else {
            ans += "a";
            for (int i = 1; i < n; i++)
                ans += "b";
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

